Description:
Prime Development Block
Situated amongst larger parcels of land this 1012m2 property is a rare find in the current market. An oldie but a goodie the much-loved, weatherboard home is located within walking distance to the shopping centre of Drysdale. Ready and waiting for the motivated renovator who loves to garden. The township of Drysdale has it all - quality health care, quality education and quality eateries ! Walk to the local tennis courts for a hit of tennis.
Drysdale is the gateway to the northern Bellarine Peninsula. A short 10 minute drive down the road to enjoy a ride on the Port Phillip Ferry for a day in Melbourne, 15 minutes to Geelong and 35 minutes to Avalon Airport. Visit the numerous cafes or drop by one of the top class local golf courses.
Located nearby are similar parcels which have been developed to accommodate quality townhouses. So many possibilities STCA.

Description:
COUNTRY FEDERATION APPEAL , COURT POSITION ON LEAFY ACRE WITH STUDIO !
A custom built home, 4 year old ,with a fabulous design and attention to detail boasting many extras, all set on native gardens creating a private haven. Immediately pleasing with large verandah and lead light entrance to wide hallway. Lounge or theatre room at the front, the master bedroom is extra generous with full ensuite and WIR, the other two are queen bedrooms both with BIR'S, 4th is set up as study, also generous proportions. Central bathroom, powder room and big laundry. The second living is a large open plan, combined with well equipped kitchen and dining, doors open to the rear decking as well as the front verandah, the solar passive influence floods light and gives a very pleasing ambiance. Features are many and Lauriston has to be inspected to see all, some include central heating, 2 split systems, high ceilings, double glazed windows, quality window furnishings and fittings, 6 star energy rating, bountiful vegetable garden, so much storage and more. Double garage with direct access to home. The freestanding studio ( flexible 2 rooms) has water and toilet with plenty of space for 2 more vehicles, caravan and or boat with bay for wash down. A perfect lifestyle home within walking distance of the Drysdale Village. Situated just a 20 minute from the city of Geelong on the Bellarine Penisula where the living is so easy, wine, dine, so many choices here you will not leave.

Description:
Tranquility in the Heart of Town
This stunning home offers relaxed family living, simply at it's best. Situated upon a whopping 969m2 block, it offers more than meets the eye and this tranquil paradise is set to impress.
Upon entry, you're greeted by the warmth of timber hardwood floors, heightened ceilings and a wide central hallway giving the home that instant grand appeal. A generously sized rumpus/2nd living area and study occupy the fore of the home and are serviced by a separate powder room. 3 spacious bedrooms lay from the central hallway, 2 with walk in robes and the 3rd offering built-in-robes. This central area is complete by a fully equipped laundry with ample storage and outside access, separate toilet and the main bathroom.
The grand master bedroom is a blissful parents retreat! Overlooking the established back garden, it offers private access to the back veranda, large walk-in-robe and lavish ensuite with double vanity, separate toilet, oversized shower & a tiled in feature spa bath. The heart of the home is at the rear and you'll instantly fall in love with the free flowing and light filled space. Comprising a large living/dining area and completed by an updated kitchen which offers a gas cook top, electric oven, dishwasher, ample storage and it's own built-in compost station. French double doors from this area offers effortless indoor/outdoor entertaining as you're welcomed by a large partial wrap around veranda, which leads you to a separate and private court yard area. The backyard offers a lush open grass area, mature fruit trees, established tree's, rain water tank and a garden shed, all while backing onto the valley offering that true tranquil atmosphere.
Other features of the home include - Over sized double lock up garage with rear access, evaporative cooling, ducted heating, solar panels and side access for boats, trailers and everything in between.
Perfectly positioned in the heart of The Bellarine, all amenities on offer are at your fingertips! Schools, shops, cafes, public transport and within proximity to the Bay, boat ramp, world class wineries and beaches, this home offers that serene lifestyle that is so highly sought after, but rarely found.

Description:
Opportunity isnt knocking its BANGING the door down!!!!!!
Make no mistake - opportunities like this are rarer than hens' teeth! Located in the heart of Drysdale, strike while the iron is hot as such opportunities are often sought but rarely found. Live in, extend, develop or subdivide (STCA) - the choice is really yours!
The 1960's solid built home has been lovingly refurbished; however still holds that charming period feel, with timber floor boards & high ceilings throughout. You are welcomed by a sundrenched formal lounge room, which freely flows into the separate dining and kitchen area. The kitchen offers a stunning feature timber island bench, electric cooking, stainless steel dishwasher and ample cupboards. 3 generous sized bedrooms are on offer and all sit from the central hallway, with 2 offering large built-in-robes. A central bathroom with bath and shower, separate toilet and a large laundry with storage completes this neat package.
Other features of the home include - Central heating, recent refurbishment, freshly painted, low maintenance gardens and a separate single garage.
Sitting on a whopping 1175m2, this unique parcel of land offers endless opportunities. The existing home could be lived in as is or extended upon to make the most of the block and perfect for the growing family who want that central Drysdale location and with enough room for all their toys. This could also be the perfect opportunity for developers to take advantage of the large block size and central location for their next project (STCA).
One thing is for sure - location is forever! A short stroll down the road and you're in central Drysdale, with all cafes, shops, schools and public transport on offer. With the Bay, Boat Ramp, Golf Clubs, flanked for choice when it comes to Wineries and beaches all at your fingertips, why wouldn't you want to take this rare chance to secure your piece of the booming Bellarine Peninsula!

Description:
Prime Property Oozing Country Charm
Tucked away in the sought-after area of James Court in Drysdale is this evergiving, double-storey, solid family home set on approximately 840sqm. With striking features such as exposed brickwork, Tasmanian Oak timber ceiling and stained glass windows this property oozes country charm. Six bedrooms with a study, there is ample room for a growing brood. As well as a downstairs bedroom suite ready for holiday renting, ageing parents or an enviable teenager retreat. ‘One of the first houses built on the street. It has been a great spot to raise our children,’ says the current owner. This is a home with easy family living and entertaining at its heart. With a large, undercover al fresco area that looks out to a well-established garden of greenery, fruit trees and a striking oak tree as its centrepiece. There’s even a chook shed and room for a firepit. The rear driveway access means there is ample boat, caravan or trailer parking and children’s play can spill out to the adjoining reserve. Nestled next to the main living, dining and kitchen zone is what could be your new favourite spot, a sunny nook to relax, unwind and read the next bestseller. The hub of the home has a three-seater breakfast bar, stainless steel appliances and generous walk-in-pantry. Upstairs houses a lavish master suite with a generous bedroom, en suite with walk-in shower, WIR, bar fridge and private balcony overlooking Corio Bay. This is where you’ll escape.

Description:
CONVENIENTLY LOCATED AND CENTRAL TOWNHOUSE
Rarely does a townhouse of this quality become available so close to the centre of Drysdale. It simply demands your attention. Whether you are investing, looking to downsize or entering the property market for the first time - this home needs to be high on your wish list. Two bedroom town houses rarely come any better and it is a credit to the local builder. Completed in 2010, this 14 square Glenvale home on 279m2 is deceptively spacious. Open plan kitchen featuring stainless steel gas cooktop and appliances is the hub of the home with conversations held around the island bench. A tiled dining area also houses a study or craft work space with plenty of storage. Ducted heating and split system cooling/heating modifies the environment for year round comfort. North facing carpeted living areas capture the natural light. High ceilings add to the depth of space and enrich the homely feel. Leading of the carpeted entrance and hallway. Bedroom one has a two way bathroom and super large walk in robe, surely only the most avid fashionista or compulsive shopper could ever dream to fill. The second bedroom has full en-suite and walk in robe. One of 5 townhouses on the site, the gardens are of low maintenance and won't take much of a green thumb to manage. A covered outdoor deck is big enough for patio dining and a BBQ which leads down to a fully fenced courtyard suitable for a small dog. While there is direct access from the garage the car may not get much use as you're only 140m to cafes and public transport, 200m to the medical centre and High street shopping, 300m to the expansive Parklands of McLeods Waterholes Reserve and 400m walk to the supermarket.

Description:
EXCLUSIVE LIFESTYLE PROPERTY
Tucked away peacefully in a rural living Bellarine Peninsula position, you’ll find this most exclusive lifestyle property set on just over an acre of land. This magnificent family residence displays exceptional designer finishes & utilises open plan living that enjoys a seamless indoor-outdoor transition, opening onto to the expansive entertaining deck & outdoor kitchen with Pizza oven. The magically positioned in-ground solar heated pool is surrounded by lush gardens and a poolside Balinese Hut to make the most of the warmer seasons looking out onto the purpose-built outdoor play area with an expansive grassed yard to kick the footy. This spacious home features a Master with a full size en-suite and 4 further bedrooms also having modern pendant bedside lighting and large WIRs. The large sleeping quarters are coupled with multiple living zones and a huge study, allowing large families to have space to move about freely as well having spaces for quiet retreat. An additional free-standing 18.8m x 9m shed with a height clearance of 3.6m & 3 phase power creates additional vehicle storage to the double garage attached to the main residence and includes a fully functioning man cave/games room with wet bar, being a perfect complement to the internal living spaces & is ideal for entertaining during the winter months. For those looking to work from home, this space can be utilized as a home office allowing privacy from the main house. Comfort and lifestyle features include; polished hardwood timber floors throughout, evaporative cooling, ducted heating, ducted vacuum and slow combustion fire. With the feeling of being secluded in a rural lifestyle and in walking distance to the Drysdale township, this property sits a pleasant 20-minute drive from Victoria’s 2nd largest city and close to golf courses, world class eateries and renowned Bellarine Peninsula wineries.

Description:
The Rail Trail At Your Back Gate!
If you love an outdoors lifestyle, this relaxed family home will tick all the right boxes- from the mountains of space greeting you at the front door, to the direct access out the back to the rail trail!
Whether it’s for family life or entertaining visitors you’ll appreciate the versatility of this modern floorplan, so central to Drysdale, coastal towns and award winning wineries of the Bellarine.
-Set on 827sqm approx. in an established, quiet and central Drysdale street that sees only local traffic
-Versatile floorplan offers optimal open living spaces with fantastic bones for future updates
-Step out the back gate to the Bellarine Rail Trail, for walks and rides to Queenscliff or Geelong
-Ready for summer BBQs the central living zone and kitchen extends to the big covered patio
-Screening trees provide privacy when entertaining, with calming green-belt views to the south
-Set back from the street with neat lawns and gardens, with plenty of parking when it’s needed
-Roomy formal lounge gifts a feeling of spaciousness upon entry and provides a quiet retreat to relax
-Family kitchen equipped with F&P dish drawers, Westinghouse appliances and casual island seating
-Corner pantry, wide family fridge cavity, plenty of cupboard and bench space is perfect for families
-The huge backyard enjoys an uninterrupted rural aspect, with plenty of room for a pool (STCA)
-See the steam train wind its way past- with sounds and smells sparking child-like excitement in all!
-Privately zoned master bedroom features WIR and full ensuite, minor bedrooms with BIRs
-Versatile study/4th BR adjoins OP living and dining, perfect as a guest bedroom or toy room
-Reverse cycle heating/cooling along with ducted gas heating keeps it cosy all year round
-Enviable laundry lets plenty of light in with glass slider, boasting huge linen and broom stores
-DLUG with int. entry as well as a double garage with driveway to securely store a boat/caravan
-Clifton Springs boat ramp and foreshore is just down the road, for great fishing and beach walks
-Walk to Lake Lorne Reserve with kids and pets, into cafes in town for a coffee or some shopping
-A ride to first class schools and colleges, 25’ to Geelong and 10’ to the Portarlington Ferry
Life in this asset rich location will ensure there is never a dull moment, experience the best of the Bellarine Peninsula all from your own back gate! Inspect today
